      },
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is used. Model form confidence is explicitly documented as LOW: the power-law exponents were calibrated on Couette-flow data and have not been independently validated for the complex, time-varying shear histories present in centrifugal pumps. This limitation is openly stated in the evidence record. The wide Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds on NIH predictions (factor of 2.5 at 95th percentile) directly reflect this low model-form confidence. Despite the low confidence, the model form is the current regulatory standard and the uncertainty is fully propagated; level 2 is achieved and meets the required level for this factor."
